TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi abstract beforefieldinit ProtocolImporter extends System.Object

Docs.summary: Provides common functionality across communication protocols for generating classes for Web services.

remarks.format: ## Remarks The abstract ProtocolImporter class and its concrete derived classes generate client proxy code or abstract server code according to a specified communication protocol. ProtocolImporter provides common functionality regardless of the protocol. Within a given protocol, a concrete derived class generates a class for each supported binding defined in a Web Services Description Language (WSDL) document. Typically, instead of directly invoking classes derived from ProtocolImporter, a developer uses these classes indirectly through the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionImporter> class.

Docs.param: An enumeration value that represents a transmission pattern.
Docs.summary: When overridden in a derived class, determines whether the current operation's operation flow is supported.

remarks.format:
## Remarks When generating code, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the IsOperationFlowSupported method to determine whether to generate a method for the current operation, as represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.Operation%2A> property. This evaluation takes place for each operation in a binding for which a class is being generated. If a `false` value is returned, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls its <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.UnsupportedOperationWarning%2A> method.
For more information, see the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.OperationMessageCollection.Flow%2A> property. The <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.Operation.Messages%2A> property is of type <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.OperationMessageCollection>.
